Most platforms will require you to logout and back in so that the system `PATH` can be set correctly.

* Installing Go on OS X

Installing Go on OS X (also known as `darwin`) can be accomplished with

*Mac*OS*Installer*

The Go project provides a `.pkg` installer:

.link https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.8.1.darwin-amd64.pkg

*Homebrew*

If you use Homebrew to manage third party software on your Mac:

 brew install golang

*MacPorts*

If you use MacPorts or Fink to manage third party software on your Mac:

 sudo port install go
 sudo fink install go

* Installing Go on Windows

*MSI*Installer*

The Go project provides a `.msi` installer for 32bit and 64bit Windows:

.link https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.8.1.windows-amd64.msi Windows 64bit MSI installer
.link https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.8.1.windows-386.msi Windows 32bit MSI installer

*.zip*file* (not recommended)

The Go project provides a `.zip` file of the Go compiler and standard library:

.link https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.8.1.windows-amd64.zip Windows 64bit zip file
.link https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.8.1.windows-386.zip Windows 32bit zip file

