* Installing Go on Linux

Depending on your Linux distribution they may have an up to date version of Go, but this is rare.  For example, RHEL7 is currently two releases behind the curve.

The most reliable way to install the latest (64bit) version of Go is to:

- Download [[https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.8.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz]]
- Change to the `/usr/local` directory.
- Untar the downloaded file.
- Add `/usr/local/go/bin` to your `PATH`:

 % echo "PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin" >> ~/.bash_profile

