* Conditional statements

Go has two conditional statements, `if` and `switch`.

`if` is used to choose between true and false branches based on a _condition_.

 if v > 0 {
         println("v is greater than zero")
 } else {
         println("v is less than or equal to zero")
 }

The body of the `else` block may be omitted. This is very common when checking preconditions of a function.

 if v == 0 {
         // nothing to do
         return
 }
 // handle v

