_Note_: In Go an empty string is `""`, not `NULL`, or `null`, or `nil`.

* Integer types

Integer types are the second most common type in Go.

Integer types come in two varieties; _signed_ and _unsigned_.

Integer types also come in several sizes, represented by the number of bits they represent.

- Signed integers: `int8`, `int16`, `int32`, `int64`.
- Unsigned integers: `uint8`, `uint16`, `uint32`, `uint64`.

Go has two integer types whose size depends on the platform you used to build your Go program:

- `int`, alias for `int32` or `int64` depending on platform.
- `uint`, alias for `uint32` or `uint64` depending on platform.

